-- Alpha Bank to Sell 30% Stake in Foreign Units, Real News Reports
-- B y   P a u l   T u g w e l l
-- 2012-04-08T09:49:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-08/alpha-bank-to-sell-30-stake-in-foreign-units-real-news-reports.html
Alpha Bank SA (ALPHA)  is close to agreeing
to sell a stake of as much as 30 percent in its east European
units to the  European Bank for Reconstruction and Development ,
 Real News  reported, without saying how it got the information.  Alpha Bank plans to separate its units in  Romania , Ukraine,
 Serbia ,  Bulgaria , Albania and Macedonia from their Greek parent
and place them into a holding company in which the EBRD would
buy a stake, the Athens-based newspaper said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Tugwell in Athens at 
 ptugwell1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jerrold Colten at 
 jcolten@bloomberg.net  